♪Is a perfect day with love♪

21
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:17,160
[The Legend of TAOTIE]

22
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:20,080
[Episode 23]

23
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,270
Wan'er! Wan'er!

24
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,000
We haven't seen for years.

25
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,600
I miss you every day.

26
00:02:44,470 --> 00:02:46,960
I happened to get a treasure
and I want to give it to you.

27
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:48,600
When the crescent rises,

28
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,440
I'll meet you by the reed pond.

29
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:56,270
Mr. Chen,

30
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,720
can you recognize

31
00:02:59,270 --> 00:03:00,320
this handwriting?

32
00:03:01,470 --> 00:03:02,320
Yes, of course.

33
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:04,670
I wrote this note.

34
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,630
Her Grace once helped me.

35
00:03:09,670 --> 00:03:11,320
Under no circumstances would I kill her.

36
00:03:12,190 --> 00:03:12,830
I have

37
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:14,390
repeated this many times.

38
00:03:15,110 --> 00:03:16,160
I trust you.

39
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,470
Yundun,

40
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,600
what do you call this?

41
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:23,600
Comb.

42
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:25,960
Mr. Chen,

43
00:03:27,190 --> 00:03:28,750
what do you call this?

44
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,160
Fine-toothed comb.

45
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:35,720
If I ask anyone out there,

46
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:38,360
they'll call this "comb".

47
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,800
Throughout Wuxia...

48
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:41,750
No.

49
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:43,630
Throughout the South,

50
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,880
people call it "comb".

51
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:49,240
Official Cai figured it out.

52
00:03:49,670 --> 00:03:51,600
People in the former dynasty
call it "fine-toothed comb".

53
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:52,830
Now,

54
00:03:52,830 --> 00:03:55,000
only people in some remote villages

55
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,440
with inconvenient communication

56
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,720
call it "fine-toothed comb".

57
00:04:00,110 --> 00:04:00,830
Mr. Chen,

58
00:04:01,670 --> 00:04:04,000
let me guess,

59
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:08,440
you're from Panyun Village
of Weiyi Mountain, right?

60
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,000
What if I am?

61
00:04:13,110 --> 00:04:14,000
What if I'm not?

62
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,270
What a coincidence.

63
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,760
I know another two men
from Panyun Village.

64
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:22,670
Ge Liang.

65
00:04:25,110 --> 00:04:26,270
A draper in the north of the city.

66
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:29,110
Ten years ago, he moved in here.

67
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,320
Half a month ago, he argued with me

68
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,880
in Pingyue House.

69
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,350
Later, he was strangled in an alley.

70
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,550
Li Jiuzeng.

71
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,880
He was a ruffian on Xingshan Street.

72
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:42,230
He bullied people and did evil.

73
00:04:42,350 --> 00:04:44,390
Seven days ago,
he ate the Hibiscus Flame

74
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:46,640
and self-ignited on the street.

75
00:04:46,790 --> 00:04:47,830
It's back.

76
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:50,950
I know it's back.

77
00:04:52,350 --> 00:04:53,480
I sent my men

78
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,950
to ask his neighbors.

79
00:04:55,550 --> 00:04:56,110
They were told

80
00:04:56,790 --> 00:04:59,230
he usually called this comb

81
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,830
"fine-toothed comb".

82
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:04,920
We also figured out something.

83
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:06,760
Her Grace

84
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:10,920
is also from Panyun Village.

85
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,070
What a coincidence.

86
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:17,040
They're from the same village.

87
00:05:18,670 --> 00:05:19,270
Mr. Chen,

88
00:05:19,270 --> 00:05:21,480
are you involved

89
00:05:22,110 --> 00:05:23,760
in their death?

90
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,480
It's just a coincidence.

91
00:05:29,230 --> 00:05:31,440
Perfect excuse.

92
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:34,160
I wonder

93
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,350
if you've heard about a story.

94
00:05:38,550 --> 00:05:39,480
An orphan

95
00:05:40,110 --> 00:05:43,070
was always bullied in his village.

96
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,790
One day,

97
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:47,830
he brought in rosefinches.

98
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:49,070
A couple of rosefinches.

99
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,350
The entire Panyun Village

100
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:53,760
was almost destroyed in a fire!

101
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:00,480
The village head asked Wuxia for help.

102
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:02,110
Archers were sent
to kill the male rosefinch.

103
00:06:02,110 --> 00:06:02,920
The female rosefinch

104
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:06,830
then disappeared.

105
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:12,350
Mr. Chen,

106
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:14,000
does this story

107
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,950
sound very familiar?

108
00:06:20,670 --> 00:06:21,920
I sent archers

109
00:06:22,230 --> 00:06:25,040
to check the destroyed village,

110
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:29,000
only to find Ge Liang
was the son of the village head.

111
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:32,760
Li Jiuzeng was his follower.

112
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,640
When they were in the village,

113
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:38,320
they always bullied the weak.

114
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:40,230
I heard

115
00:06:40,510 --> 00:06:42,760
the orphan they bullied most

116
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:45,070
was also a Chen.

117
00:06:47,510 --> 00:06:48,000
No.

118
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:49,510
It's not me.

119
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:50,480
It's not.

120
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,110
I wouldn't kill anyone.

121
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:53,160
I...

122
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:54,600
I wouldn't kill Her Grace.

123
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:56,480
Oh, I see.

124
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:57,670
It's them.

125
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,670
The rosefinches.

126
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:01,160
They killed these people.

127
00:07:02,390 --> 00:07:04,600
You snatched money from Ge Liang's bag.

128
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,880
You killed him!

129
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,230
He didn't give me the money.

130
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:08,600
I had to do that.

131
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,720
You just admitted that.

132
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:22,600
And Li Jiuzeng...

133
00:07:24,270 --> 00:07:26,160
What witchcraft did you use

134
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,950
to make him self-ignite?

135
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,200
How did Her Grace offend you?

136
00:07:32,070 --> 00:07:33,760
Why did you kill her?

137
00:07:35,270 --> 00:07:36,070
It's not me.

138
00:07:36,390 --> 00:07:37,480
It's just not.

139
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:39,550
I wouldn't kill Wan'er.

140
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:41,110
She's the woman

141
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:43,070
I've been loving.

142
00:07:43,550 --> 00:07:45,110
I wouldn't kill her.

143
00:07:45,110 --> 00:07:47,110
I wouldn't kill my beloved woman.

144
00:07:47,110 --> 00:07:48,880
I just wouldn't.

145
00:07:49,110 --> 00:07:49,600
How dare you?

146
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,600
You can't call Her Grace by name.

147
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:00,040
What's so funny?

148
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:06,040
What's so funny?

149
00:08:07,670 --> 00:08:09,390
Your mistake is funny!

150
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:15,510
Wan'er and I were very close

151
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:16,880
and we grew up together.

152
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,830
I would rather die for her

153
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:20,550
than hurt her.

154
00:08:24,230 --> 00:08:25,350
It's hard to tell.

155
00:08:27,350 --> 00:08:31,390
His Highness is charming.

156
00:08:32,230 --> 00:08:34,280
Her Grace would marry him.

157
00:08:35,230 --> 00:08:37,910
So, she wouldn't like you anymore.

158
00:08:42,150 --> 00:08:43,910
When she rejected you,

159
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,960
anger flooded through you

160
00:08:46,550 --> 00:08:48,640
and you may also burn her

161
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,840
with the rosefinch's flame.

162
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:50,790
Nonsense!

163
00:08:51,230 --> 00:08:52,230
Total nonsense!

164
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,080
How could you slander me?

165
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,710
If I had the flame,

166
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,520
I would burn you first!

167
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:03,520
Sadly...

168
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:06,550
Sadly, I'm not powerful enough.

169
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:09,520
But anyway,

170
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,710
you can never get the truth

171
00:09:12,710 --> 00:09:13,710
from me.

172
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,960
Keep investigating it.

173
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:21,150
If I had the flame,

174
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:22,200
I'd burn you

175
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,080
and eat you up!

176
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:23,670
You'll never know

177
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:25,030
how tasty it can be!

178
00:09:25,150 --> 00:09:26,640
I'll even chew your bones

179
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:27,710
and then...

180
00:10:00,590 --> 00:10:01,230
Who's that?

181
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:06,280
You're agile, Mr. Lu.

182
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,150
Your Highness.

183
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:15,760
I've never been here.

184
00:10:16,030 --> 00:10:17,590
You've never seen me.

185
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,150
Don't bother to greet me.

186
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:20,230
I understand.

187
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,440
Are you done interrogating Chen Ze?

188
00:10:22,910 --> 00:10:23,840
Did he confess

189
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,760
he murdered Wan'er?

190
00:10:27,470 --> 00:10:28,400
Chen Ze is insane.

191
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,320
His speech is quite suspicious.

192
00:10:30,710 --> 00:10:31,670
He may not be the killer.

193
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,590
I need to investigate more.

194
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:38,440
Li Wan'er is the princess.

195
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:40,910
She was killed
in the wild for no reason.

196
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:44,790
But you fail to solve this case quickly.

197
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:47,760
Your Highness,

198
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,790
my job is to arrest the real killer.

199
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:53,350
Before Chen Ze is convicted,

200
00:10:54,110 --> 00:10:56,440
he's a common man.

201
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,550
Killing a commoner

202
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:01,320
won't help with this case.

203
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:02,910
How dare you disobey me

204
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,670
for a shameless guy?

205
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:14,520
Fine.

206
00:11:15,790 --> 00:11:16,790
You have two days.

207
00:11:17,670 --> 00:11:18,880
Within two days,

208
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,670
you must find the real killer.

209
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:22,400
Yes.

210
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:33,920
[Sealed by the Inspection Department]

211
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,350
Why is Tianxiang Restaurant closed down?

212
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:43,550
Look. It's closed down.

213
00:11:43,550 --> 00:11:44,080
I heard

214
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,200
another person died after eating

215
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,280
the Hibiscus Flame.

216
00:11:47,150 --> 00:11:47,710
Really?

217
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:48,440
What's worse,

218
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,280
it was the princess

219
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:51,880
who would marry His Highness.

220
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:52,760
Really?

221
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:54,110
It's big trouble, then.

222
00:11:58,230 --> 00:11:59,030
Miss Zhu,

223
00:11:59,590 --> 00:12:01,080
what's going on?

224
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:01,710
Yeah.

225
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:05,590
Her Grace disappeared before the feast.

226
00:12:05,590 --> 00:12:07,350
Why is our dish involved?

227
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:09,520
Anyway, our restaurant and Miss Zhu

228
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:11,230
are blamed for this.

229
00:12:11,550 --> 00:12:13,280
His Highness turned
against us so quickly.

230
00:12:14,470 --> 00:12:15,590
He isn't to blame.

231
00:12:15,910 --> 00:12:17,320
Even I think it's unbelievable.

232
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:19,080
Did Her Grace...

233
00:12:20,110 --> 00:12:21,910
Did she also eat
the rosefinch's egg before?

234
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:22,760
Yes.

235
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:25,590
Such a strange coincidence.

236
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:29,400
I told you.

237
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,110
Don't cook anything

238
00:12:30,110 --> 00:12:31,440
so dangerous.

239
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,350
There aren't so many coincidences.

240
00:12:34,590 --> 00:12:35,880
Actually,

241
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,470
everyone makes his own choice.

242
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:40,470
But...

243
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:42,960
Why did he send Mingyan

244
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:45,230
instead of coming personally?

245
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:47,470
Someone died.

246
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:48,760
Why do you still think of him?

247
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:50,960
His fiancée just died.

248
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:51,790
Qing, you sound

249
00:12:51,790 --> 00:12:53,080
really unsympathetic.

250
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,670
I pitied him,

251
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:56,320
so I blamed you.

252
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,910
His Highness just lost his fiancée.

253
00:12:58,110 --> 00:12:59,440
He must be grieved.

254
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,670
How can he see you now?

255
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,320
Does he have to come here

256
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,440
and confront you?

257
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:05,910
He can do that.

258
00:13:06,230 --> 00:13:07,520
It may not be my fault.

259
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:09,670
Too sad for Wan'er.

260
00:13:12,550 --> 00:13:13,150
Forget it.

261
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,110
It's not too bad.

262
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:15,080
Qing,

263
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,080
let me show you something.

264
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:27,350
Bai Ze's Supernatural Creatures?

265
00:13:28,110 --> 00:13:28,880
Miss Zhu,

266
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:31,200
how did you get it back?

267
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:32,960
Yesterday, at Heng's mansion,

268
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:34,200
Wan'er gave it to me.

269
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:35,550
Her Grace?

270
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:37,790
The one who defeated me

271
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:39,640
and stole it was really agile.

272
00:13:39,790 --> 00:13:40,960
It can't be Her Grace.

273
00:13:41,670 --> 00:13:43,110
Among the guards

274
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,520
who serve His Highness,
many of them are very agile.

275
00:13:45,910 --> 00:13:47,000
So, His Highness

276
00:13:47,790 --> 00:13:49,400
must be involved.

277
00:13:52,910 --> 00:13:53,550
Miss Zhu,

278
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:55,960
what else did Her Grace tell you?

279
00:14:25,230 --> 00:14:25,880
Miss Zhu,

280
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:27,910
it's...

281
00:14:37,350 --> 00:14:38,150
When Official Xu

282
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:39,550
gave it to me,

283
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:40,080
I thought

284
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,790
it could echo the Dragon's blood.

285
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:43,150
But only Jiao was there.

286
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:45,640
It appears so now.

287
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,960
Everything in this world is complicated.

288
00:14:50,350 --> 00:14:52,640
No one knows what will happen

289
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:53,960
at a certain time.

290
00:14:57,440 --> 00:15:00,400
It's the Hibiscus Flame
I made for Wan'er yesterday.

291
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:02,200
